Reunion of Separated Families and Relatives Closes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mt. Kumgang Resort, June 30 (KCNA) -- The 14th reunion of separated families and relatives which began on June 19 continued in Mt. Kumgang Resort.
 The separated families and relatives from the north made a group reunion with those from the south on June 25.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Min Kyong Chun, Han Kyu Bin and others from the north told those from the south that all the people should turn out in the struggle for great national unity and the reunification of the country under the banner of "By our nation itself".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Separated families and relatives from the north and the south had a group reunion on June 28. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were overcome with deep emotion as they had longed to reunite with each other even in dreams. They talked with each other about the course of their life, inquired after those who were not able to join them and conveyed tidings from them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam from the north, together with his wife, daughter and son, reunited with his mother and sister from the south, sharing warm kindred feelings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was happy to offer the 80th birthday spread to his mother and present wild insam, clothing materials and other souvenirs to his mother and sister. And he shared with them his pent-up inmost thoughts in a family atmosphere. He was also interviewed by south Korean reporters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The separated families and relatives from the north and the south earnestly urged all other fellow countrymen to pool wisdom and energies and hand over a reunified country to posterity without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the group reunion kinsmen from the north and the south had family reunions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Central Committee of the DPRK Red Cross Society and the Red Cross of south Korea gave a reception for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During their reunion arranged on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of the historic June 15 joint declaration, kinsmen from the north and the south had meals together in a harmonious family atmosphere and toured the scenic area of Samil Lagoon.

DPRK's Self-Defensive Steps Favored 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- We fully support all the self-defensive steps taken by socialist Korea to defend its territory and the dignity and honor of the nation from the U.S. imperialists' aggression under the condition that the U.S. is constantly threatening the DPRK.
 The Asian Regional Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, the All-India Indo-Korean Friendship Association and the Indian Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification said this in a joint statement issued on June 24 on the occasion of the month of international solidarity with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. troops stationed in south Korea are the main obstacle standing in the way of peaceful reunification of Korea, the statement said, stressing that they will demand immediate withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea and stir up public opinions for peaceful reunification of Korea, the ardent desire of all the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Niculae Pavelescu, chairman of the Executive Committee of the Left United Party of Romania, issued a statement on June 27 on the occasion of the June 25-July 27 month of the anti-U.S. joint struggle. He said in the statement that the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il is the most powerful weapon to counter the U.S. policy of strength and a just political mode to ensure peace and security in Asia and achieve the reunification of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that his party will in the future, too, stand on the side of the Korean people who are waging a dynamic struggle for socialist construction and the independent and peaceful reunification of the country under the banner of Songun and actively support their struggle.

Rodong Sinmun on Anti-U.S. Struggle of South Koreans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- The nation-wide movement for independent national reunification requires to put an end to the U.S. policy of making south Korea into its military base and drive the U.S. imperialist aggressors out of south Korea, which is a vital issue related to the destiny of the nation and an urgent demand of the times that brooks no further delay. 
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military presence in south Korea is a brigandish act of violating the demand and desire of all the Korean people for national independence and sovereignty and a vicious crime of turning south Korea into a springboard and an advanced base for a war of aggression and blocking the reunification and independent and unified progress of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. struggle in south Korea is rapidly developing into a mass struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people's awareness of anti-U.S. independence growing after the adoption of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration gives impetus to an extensive anti-U.S. struggle. Most of south Koreans regard the U.S. as the biggest obstacle standing in the way of reunification and assert that the U.S., not the north, should be designated as the principal enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. struggle is now becoming a common slogan transcending class and strata, affiliation and position, progress and conservatism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. struggle of south Koreans has recently intensified and developed in broad and diverse forms in combination with the movement for reunification.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The movement for national reunification in Korea is inseparably linked with the anti-U.S. struggle. It is impossible to achieve national reunification without the anti-U.S. struggle. It is none other than the U.S, who has divided Korea into two and kept its troops stationed in south Korea, standing in the way of Korea's reunification for more than 60 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people are intensifying their struggle, converting different forms of the movement for national reunification into the anti-U.S. struggle this year, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What draws attention in their anti-U.S. struggle is that international support and solidarity with it are increasing day by day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. struggle is the requirement of the times and the unanimous desire of all the fellow countrymen. Voices demanding the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea are growing in the U.S., too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should stop its anachronistic policy of domination over south Korea, its moves to make it a military base and take a bold decision to withdraw its aggression troops from south Korea.

Kim Jong Il Sends Message of Greetings to Hu Jintao 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il Friday sent a message of greetings to Hu Jintao, General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, on the occasion of the 85th founding anniversary of the CPC.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I send warmest congratulations to you and, through you, to the Central Committee of the CPC and all the members of it and the Chinese people on the occasion of the 85th anniversary of the CPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The founding of the CPC was an epochal event which opened up a new chapter in the long history of the Chinese nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The founding of the CPC enabled the working people of China to have a genuine guiding vanguard organization and traverse the path of sacred struggle and creation to achieve the class liberation and the country's prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The CPC led a series of arduous revolutionary wars against imperialist powers and domestic reactionaries to great victories and built new socialist China in the vast land of China. It has achieved great successes in the socialist modernization drive with Chinese characteristics and in the efforts to accomplish the cause of reunifying the whole country and remarkably increased the international position and role of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The credit for the amazing changes now taking place in China goes to the CPC which laid down a correct line and policies suited to its actual conditions and in line with the requirements of the Chinese people and powerfully aroused all of them to carry them out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 85 year-long proud history of the CPC goes to prove that there is neither the present of new China nor its rosier future without the CPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our party and people are rejoiced over all the successes made by the CPC and the fraternal Chinese people as over their own and extend sincere congratulations to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I wholeheartedly hope that the collective leadership of the CPC with you as general secretary will achieve fresh and greater success in the efforts to build a comprehensively well-off and harmoniously developed socialist society and accomplish the cause of complete reunification of the country by preserving the progressive nature of the party, increasing its governing ability and leading the party and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-China friendship, which was provided by the revolutionary forerunners of the two countries in the course of the joint struggle and bequeathed to their peoples as a precious legacy, has made an important contribution to giving a powerful impetus to socialist construction in the two countries and ensuring peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the invariable stand of our Party to steadily develop the DPRK-China friendship which is deeply rooted in the hearts of the two peoples and which stood all tests of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is my belief that this traditional friendship will grow stronger in all fields in the future, too, thanks to the joint efforts of the two parties and the two peoples.

Month of Anti- U.S. Joint Struggle Observed in Mexico and France 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- Functions for solidarity with the Korean people including meetings were held by the Mexican Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification and the France-Korea Friendship Association on June 23 and 24 on the occasion of the month of anti-U.S. joint struggle (June 25-July 27).
 Alejandro Rosales Sanchez, chairman of the Mexican Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, in a speech at a meeting praised President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il for their immortal exploits performed in the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the adoption and publication of the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and its historical significance and tremendous vitality and the nature of the issue of Korea's reunification, he urged the U.S. to stop interfering in that issue and withdraw its forces and nuclear weapons from south Korea as early as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Andre Aubry, delegate president of the France-Korea Friendship Association, noted that under the leadership of Kim Il Sung the heroic Korean People's Army and the Korean people won a shining victory in the Korean war by defeating for the first time in history U.S. imperialism, which sought to dominate the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, expressed the belief that the Korean people would surely achieve the historic cause of national reunification and build a great prosperous powerful nation as they are inspired by the effective Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il and most just proposals for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A Korean film "Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks" was shown in Mexico and an art performance was given in France.

Kim Jong Il Highly Praised in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- A meeting, a lecture, a book and photo exhibition and a film show were held in Sweden and Mongolia on June 19 on the occasions of the 42nd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the 6th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and the month of anti-U.S. joint struggle (June 25-July 27).
 Christer Lundgren, chairman of the Sweden-Korea Friendship Association, in a speech at the meeting highly praised the immortal party leadership exploits performed by Kim Jong Il for the last more than four decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that the DPRK would further prosper under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il as he brought about the greatest success in the movement for Korea's reunification through the historic North-South Summit and the adoption of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and has firmly defended the socialist cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 N. Bold, chairman of the Centre for the Study of the Juche Idea of Mongolian Chinggis Khan College, said in the lecture titled "The Juche Idea and National Reunification" that under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il the DPRK has confidently advanced along the path chosen by itself, unshaken in any storm, and creditably protected the dignity of the country, resolutely frustrating the pressure and offensive of the imperialist allied forces with the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Sweden.

Halt to Military Exercises RIMPAC-2006 Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly made public a statement titled "Stop large-scale north-targeted war exercises RIMPAC" on June 26.
 The statement noted that the U.S.-led large joint military exercises RIMPAC-2006 were launched on June 25 in the waters of the Pacific and will last until July 29 as part of the moves to invade the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said that the exercises now being staged by the U.S. and its followers under the pretext of "ensuring security" in sea routes and "jointly countering terrorism" in contingency are the most provocative and dangerous war maneuvers targeted against the north in their scale and duration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Terming the participation in the war exercises against the fellow countrymen in the north in pursuance of the U.S. policy a crime against the nation, the statement called upon all the people to turn out in the actions against the exercises and for the pullback of the U.S. forces from south Korea.

Anniversary of Korean Documentary and Scientific Film Studio Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- A meeting took place at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre on Friday to mark the 60th anniversary of the Korean Documentary and Scientific Film Studio.
 A congratulatory message of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea to the creators, employees and officials of the film studio was conveyed by Yang Hyong Sop at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The congratulatory message said that President Kim Il Sung with a deep insight into the important role of the documentary and scientific films in the revolution and construction founded the film studio on July 1, Juche 35 (1946). Kim Jong Il put forward a revolutionary policy on boosting the production of documentary and scientific films as required by the process of modeling the whole society on the Juche idea and has led the struggle to implement it, the message noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The creators and officials of the film studio produced a great many revolutionary and militant documentary films and popular scientific films in the periods of the building of a new country, the Fatherland Liberation War and socialist construction. In this way they have contributed to powerfully arousing the people to the revolution and construction and accelerating the construction of socialist economy and culture. The message highly praised them for having registered successes in producing a lot of films that helped the Korean people firmly defend socialism of Juche and usher in a new era of building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report was made at the meeting to be followed by speeches.

Folk Dance Company of Russia Performs in Pyongyang
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- An art performance was given by the visiting State Academic Moiseyev Folk Dance Company of Russia at the Ponghwa Art Theatre on Friday before capacity audience.
 Appreciating the performance were Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, officials concerned and creators and artistes in the field of culture and arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Alexander Matsegora, charge d'affaires a.i., and staff members of the Russian embassy and diplomatic envoys and staff members of foreign embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian artistes gave this performance in Pyongyang in the wake of their successful performance tour of local areas in the DPRK. In the repertoire they made a truthful artistic representation of the optimistic life, national emotion and customs of the Russians and various other nations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a dance "Partisans" well known to the Korean people the performers successfully depicted the valiant struggle of the Russian people against the aggressors during the Patriotic War, meeting its ideological and thematic need. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In dances "Summer," "Small Steppe" and fleet dance suite "A Day on Warship" they made a successful artistic depiction of the Russian army and people's ardent love for the country and their optimistic life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Moldovan humorous dance "Tabakeryaska", Uzbek dance "Dance with a Plate" and other dances fully reflected the optimistic life and national customs of the peoples of different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was conveyed to the performers in congratulation of their successful performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance continues.

Anniversary of University of National Economics Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- A meeting took place on Friday to commemorate the 60th anniversary of the University of National Economics.
 Present there were Kim Ki Nam, Cabinet members, leading officials of ministries, national institutions and party cadres training institutions and teachers and students of the university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea to the teachers and students of the university was conveyed by Choe Thae Bok. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The congratulatory message said that President Kim Il Sung founded the university on July 1, Juche 35 (1946) and General Secretary Kim Jong Il has wisely led the university to improve and strengthen the work of training state economic management officials to meet the requirements of modeling the whole society on the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It highly praised the university for training many administrative and economic officials in each period of the construction of a new country, the Fatherland Liberation War, the post-war rehabilitation and construction and socialist construction so as to contribute to strengthening the people's power and successfully carrying out the revolutionary tasks of various stages and achieving great successes in the struggle to implement the WPK's policy of training cadres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report was made by Pak Son Ho, president of the university. And it was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers called upon all the teachers and students to defend and glorify the undying leadership feats of the Party and the leader associated with the university down through generations and make a tangible contribution to developing the national economy and building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation in response to the tasks set forth in the congratulatory message of the WPK Central Committee.

Rodong Sinmun Observers Anniversary of CPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today editorially observes the 85th anniversary of the Communist Party of China. The Korean people sincerely wish the fraternal Chinese people greater success in their struggle to achieve their just cause under the leadership of the CPC, the editorial says, and goes on:
 The foundation of the CPC on July 1, 1921 was a historic event of epochal significance in the Chinese revolution and the struggle of the Chinese people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was under the leadership of the CPC, genuine vanguard that the Chinese people could confidently advance along the road of struggle and change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Workers' Party and people of Korea are sincerely rejoiced at the great achievements made by the Communist Party and people of China in their struggle to build socialism and reunify the country as at their own and heartily congratulate them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The just cause of the Chinese people has a bright prospect and is making steady progress. They are staging a fresh march to attain a higher goal of the socialist modernization drive with Chinese characteristics under the leadership of the CPC with Hu Jintao as general secretary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are working hard to attain their strategic goal to build a comprehensively well-off society set by the 16th Party Congress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people sincerely wish the Communist Party and people of China greater success in their struggle to implement the strategic tasks set forth at the 16th Party Congress and extend firm solidarity to their just struggle to achieve the reunification of the whole country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the common aspiration and desire of the peoples of the two countries to boost the traditional DPRK-China friendship. The development of the DPRK-China friendly and cooperative relations is helpful to advancing the revolution and construction in the two countries, ensuring peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world and building a new just world. The DPRK-China friendship has reached a new high level in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand and invariable will of the Workers' Party and people of Korea to steadily consolidate and develop the DPRK-China friendly and cooperative relations. This traditional friendship will grow stronger thanks to the common efforts of the two parties and two peoples in the new century.

U.S. Denounced for Deploying Ultra-Modern Reconnaissance Plane in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 1 (KCNA) -- The U.S. has deployed latest "U-2 S Block 20" in south Korea, timed to coincide with its evermore undisguised military threat and blackmail against the DPRK. This is another grave military provocation against the DPRK and an extremely dangerous move for a war of aggression against it to push the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war.
 A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland said this in a statement on June 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality clearly indicates that the U.S. remains unchanged in its criminal attempt to stifle the DPRK by force of arms, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is recklessly driving the situation on the peninsula to the brink of war, preoccupied with the moves for a war against the DPRK. This grave situation once again goes to prove that peace has been preserved on the peninsula so far entirely thanks to the DPRK's strong war deterrent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that the U.S. is set to ignite a nuclear war for the purpose of disturbing peace and stability on the peninsula by force, the DPRK is compelled to bolster up its deterrent for self-defence under the uplifted banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are fully prepared to counter any provocation and challenge of the U.S.
